{"id":10171,"date":"2012-12-10T21:35:05","date_gmt":"2012-12-11T02:35:05","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=10171"},"modified":"2025-05-16T12:12:15","modified_gmt":"2025-05-16T08:12:15","slug":"malik-fiqh-force-caliph","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/12\/10\/malik-fiqh-force-caliph\/","title":{"rendered":"Malik on Fiqh: Imam Malik does not force his school on Muslims"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn &#8216;Abdul Barr reported: Imam Malik ibn Anas, may Allah have mercy upon him, said: When the Caliph Abu Ja\u2019far al-Mansur performed the pilgrimage, he called for me, so I entered upon him and he spoke to me, asking me questions, and I replied. Then, he said, \u201cI am determined to have several copies made of these books of yours. I will send a copy to every region in the lands of the Muslims. I will command them to adhere to its contents without referring to any other, and they will set aside everything but this new knowledge. Indeed, I see the foundation of knowledge in the narrations of the people of Medina and their teachings.\u201d I said, \u201cO Commander of the Faithful, do not do so, for the people have received sayings, heard reports, and transmitted various accounts. Each one holds to what it has received and acts according to it. They practice as such due to people\u2019s differences, the Companions of the Messenger of Allah and others. Turning them away from their beliefs would surely be difficult, so leave the people with what they are upon and what every country has chosen for themselves.\u201d Al-Mansur said, \u201cI swear on my life, if you had obeyed me in this matter, I would have commanded it.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Ja\u0304mi&#8217; Baya\u0304n al-&#8216;Ilm li-Ibn &#8216;Abd al-Barr 870<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0645\u0627\u0